%h2 Editing Structure and Governance
%div.hint_toggle
  About this section...
%div.hint_text{:style => 'display: none; width: 75%;'}
  %p Launching the Global Compact should be distinguished from launching the network. A public launch of the Global Compact, which is a high-level event within a country, typically takes place after a significant number of local companies have become engaged or are ready to be engaged in the initiative. Support from a critical mass of companies before the launch increases the likelihood that a GCLN will be established and that the network will be sustainable.
  %p Launching the network is essentially about institutionalizing a group of companies with a sufficient level of commitment to ensure the effective, inclusive and accountable governance system of the Global Compact initiative in a country.

